  <metadata>
    <title>Update `DeliverToIndexNodeExecutor` to write new fields (dual-write)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
RE-TARGETED per task 060 inventory §6.2/§6.3 + task 061 completion notes: the POML named
`DeliverToIndexNodeExecutor.cs`, but that file does NOT contain `sprk_searchindexed` references.
The ACTUAL writer call-sites + mapping layer were updated instead (single-choke-point per
inventory recommendation §6.2 — covers all 3 upstream writers with one model+mapping change).

FILES MODIFIED (5 production + 2 test):
  - src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/Models.cs
    Added `SearchIndexQueuedOn` + `SearchIndexCompletedOn` (DateTime?) to both `UpdateDocumentRequest`
    (line 187+) and `DocumentEntity` (line 298+); annotated legacy SearchIndexed + SearchIndexedOn
    as "PRESERVED for dual-write transition per spec line 366" with XML doc cross-references.
  - src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/DataverseWebApiService.cs
    Extended PATCH payload mapping (lines 611-620) and GET MapToDocumentEntity (lines 786-797)
    to include sprk_searchindex{queued,completed}on alongside legacy sprk_searchindexed +
    sprk_searchindexedon.
  - src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/DataverseServiceClientImpl.cs
    Extended GET column select-list (lines 120-125), UPDATE entity attribute writes (lines 530-548),
    and MapToDocumentEntityWithLookups (lines 1093-1100) for the same 2 new attributes.
  - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/Handlers/RagIndexingJobHandler.cs (line ~211)
    Completion path: dual-writes `SearchIndexCompletedOn = UtcNow` AND legacy `SearchIndexed=true`
    + `SearchIndexedOn = UtcNow` (single `completedAt` capture for consistency).
  - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/RagEndpoints.cs (lines ~558 + ~702)
    IndexFile + SendToIndex endpoints: same dual-write pattern as the handler.
  - tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Integration/DataverseEntitySchemaTests.cs
    Extended ExpectedFieldMappings with 2 new entries (Field Count test auto-extends);
    added new region "Search-Index Lifecycle Dual-Write (R3 FR-3H3.2 / AC-H3.2)" with 4 tests:
    - UpdateDocumentRequest_HasSearchIndexLifecycleProperties
    - UpdateDocumentRequest_LegacySearchIndexFieldsPreservedForDualWrite
    - BuildEntity_WithSearchIndexQueuedOnOnly_RepresentsEnqueueState
    - BuildEntity_OnCompletion_DualWritesNewAndLegacyFields
  - tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Jobs/Handlers/RagIndexingJobHandlerTests.cs
    Added new region "Search-Index Lifecycle Dual-Write (R3 FR-3H3.2 / AC-H3.2 — task 062)" with 3 tests:
    - ProcessAsync_SuccessfulIndexing_DualWritesNewAndLegacySearchIndexFields (captures UpdateDocumentRequest
      passed to IDocumentDataverseService; asserts SearchIndexCompletedOn set within
      before/after UtcNow window; legacy SearchIndexed=true; SearchIndexedOn mirrors
      CompletedOn; SearchIndexQueuedOn null; SearchIndexName unchanged)
    - ProcessAsync_IndexingFailure_DoesNotWriteCompletionFields (failure path leaves both
      new + legacy completion fields untouched — the long-standing pitfall fix)
    - ProcessAsync_DataverseUpdateFails_StillReportsSuccessfulOutcome (resilience: indexing
      success not held hostage by tracking-field write failure)

DUAL-WRITE SEMANTICS (per spec FR-3H3.2 + AC-H3.2 + spec assumption line 366):
  - ENQUEUE path: writers may set `SearchIndexQueuedOn = UtcNow`; do NOT touch `SearchIndexed`
    or `SearchIndexCompletedOn` (state = "in progress"). [Note: no current code path enqueues
    a separate "queued" stamp — the existing writers only fire on completion. The model
    supports the enqueue stamp for future Service Bus publish-site instrumentation per inventory §6.4.]
  - COMPLETION path: writers MUST dual-write — `SearchIndexCompletedOn = UtcNow` AND
    `SearchIndexed = true` AND `SearchIndexedOn = UtcNow` (single captured `completedAt`
    timestamp shared across all three for consistency). `SearchIndexName` is the routing
    field and is unchanged by this migration.
  - FAILURE path: writers leave `SearchIndexCompletedOn` null + `SearchIndexed` false/null
    (mirrors the existing failure convention — failure exits before reaching the Update call,
    or the try/catch around the Dataverse update logs warning and swallows non-fatal errors).
  - IDEMPOTENCY: PATCH semantics — re-running the completion write re-stamps both new and
    legacy fields atomically.

QUALITY GATES:
  - Build (Sprk.Bff.Api): 0 errors / 16 pre-existing warnings (unchanged vs baseline)
  - Build (test project):  0 errors / 1 pre-existing warning
  - Tests (focused — RagIndexingJobHandlerTests + DataverseEntitySchemaTests): 64/64 PASS
